      • createPrepareRequest

        public com.sun.jdi.request.ClassPrepareRequest createPrepareRequest(ClassPrepareRequestor requestor,
                                                                    SourcePosition position)
                                                             throws NoDataException
        Description copied from interface: PositionManager
        Called to request the JVM to notify the debugger engine when a class corresponding to a breakpoint location is loaded. The implementation should calculate the pattern of the class files corresponding to the breakpoint location and call RequestManager.createClassPrepareRequest(com.intellij.debugger.requests.ClassPrepareRequestor, java.lang.String) to create the request.
        Specified by:
        createPrepareRequest in interface PositionManager
        Parameters:
        requestor - the object to receive the notification from the JVM.
        position - the location of a breakpoint.
        Returns:
        the prepare request, or null if the code is managed by this PositionManager but no class prepare notification is needed
        Throws:
        NoDataException - if the position is not in the code managed by this PositionManager
